==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|fr|pantalon}}, from {{der|en|it|Pantalone}}, a traditional character in 16th-century Italian comedy. See “[[w:Commedia dell'arte|Commedia dell'arte]]” in Wikipedia. The name is of {{uder|en|grc|-}} origin and loosely translates as "entirely lion." See {{m|grc|παν}} and {{m|grc|λέων}}.

